- 'Best-selling vehicles' refers to vehicles with high total units sold; 
- 'Key performance metrics' include metrics such as maximum sale price, total units sold, average total amount, maximum resale value, maximum horsepower, average fuel efficiency, and maximum power performance factor; 
- 'Resale value depreciation of more than 5% per year' means a decrease in the resale value of the vehicle over a year, calculated as (current resale value - previous resale value) / previous resale value * 100, with a threshold of -5%; 
- 'Top 50% for speed' refers to vehicles with top speeds in the highest two quartiles (i.e., top 50%) of all vehicles.

Average fuel efficiency refers to the average miles a vehicle can travel per gallon of fuel, which is a measure of a vehicle's fuel efficiency; 
A power performance factor is a measure used to evaluate a vehicle's performance, though the exact formula is not provided here; 
Total sale amounts include the sale price and additional costs such as tax and discount.
